                        <tr>
                <td bgcolor="#f0f0f0" width="20%" valign="top"><b>Sprint:</b></td>
                <td id="customfield_10020-269557-value" class="value" bgcolor="#ffffff" width="80%">April 1 Release</td>
            </tr>
                                <tr>
                <td bgcolor="#f0f0f0" width="20%" valign="top"><b>Rank:</b></td>
                <td id="customfield_10019-269557-value" class="value" bgcolor="#ffffff" width="80%">      0|r0poul:w
  </td>
            </tr>
                                <tr>
                <td bgcolor="#f0f0f0" width="20%" valign="top"><b>Release Notes:</b></td>
                <td id="customfield_11841-269557-value" class="value" bgcolor="#ffffff" width="80%">      <p>Structured medication administration data has been added to the <tt>medication_administration</tt> data frame for the remaining health systems. As a reminder:</p>

<ul>
	<li>When available, <tt>medication_administration</tt> contains the medication administration records from the EMR (<tt>admin_source = "structured"</tt>) or abstraction (<tt>admin_source = "ma"</tt>) for patients' systemic therapies (in <tt>systemic_therapy</tt>).</li>
	<li>It does not contain medication administrations for patients without <tt>systemic_therapy</tt> data nor does it contain non-anticancer/antineoplastic medications - i.e., it is restricted to the administrations of systemic anticancer (antineoplastic) therapies for the patients with abstracted systemic therapies.</li>
	<li>Medication administration records could not be found in structured data or abstraction for all patients nor for all abstracted therapies.</li>
</ul>

  </td>
            </tr>
                                <tr>
                <td bgcolor="#f0f0f0" width="20%" valign="top"><b>Code Review:</b></td>
                <td id="customfield_12225-269557-value" class="value" bgcolor="#ffffff" width="80%"><div class="shorten" id="customfield_12225-field">
                        <span class="tinylink">        <span class="user-hover" rel="ug:122d8429-4cb9-4247-8547-aa472f2bdbd8" id="multiuser_cf_ug:122d8429-4cb9-4247-8547-aa472f2bdbd8">Brian Carter</span></span>            </div>
</td>
            </tr>
                                <tr>
                <td bgcolor="#f0f0f0" width="20%" valign="top"><b>Release Priority:</b></td>
                <td id="customfield_12224-269557-value" class="value" bgcolor="#ffffff" width="80%">    High - required for customer need, blocker for future dev, bug
</td>
            </tr>
                                <tr>
                <td bgcolor="#f0f0f0" width="20%" valign="top"><b>Data Review (migrated):</b></td>
                <td id="customfield_12226-269557-value" class="value" bgcolor="#ffffff" width="80%"><div class="shorten" id="customfield_12226-field">
                        <span class="tinylink">        <span class="user-hover" rel="b3a562d6-6e2a-4835-a18d-c160b27567ce" id="multiuser_cf_b3a562d6-6e2a-4835-a18d-c160b27567ce">Monika Izano</span></span>            </div>
</td>
            </tr>
            </table>

    <br/>

    <table cellpadding="2" cellspacing="0" border="0" width="100%" align="center">
    <tr>
        <td bgcolor="#bbbbbb" width="1%" nowrap align="center">
            &nbsp;<font color="#ffffff"><b>Description</b></font>&nbsp;
        </td>
        <td>&nbsp;</td>
    </tr>
    </table>

    <table cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" border="0" width="100%">
    <tr>
        <td id="descriptionArea">
            <p>Once MedicationRequest data is available for all Enriched ADS patients for Advent, BH, and MLH, we need to create/expand the pipeline to get, clean, wrangle, and derive that data for the <tt>medication_administration</tt> concept in ADS (see <tt>ads/utilities/functions/med_admin.R</tt>). I anticipate MedicationRequest needing its own set of <tt>get_</tt> and <tt>clean_</tt> functions. The existing <tt>wrangle_med_admin</tt> and <tt>derive_med_admin</tt> can pipeline should be expanded for this new data source.</p>

<p><b>Important notes</b></p>

<ul>
	<li><b><em>If not performed separately by ADS-409: Coverage - do this as soon as possible, even an imperfect number will be helpful</em></b>
	<ul>
		<li>Please check <tt>N of patients with matched admin</tt> / <tt>N of patients with systemic therapy</tt> overall, by health system, and by cohort</li>
		<li>If we have low coverage (due to problems similar to Aurora’s), then we need to start game planning for this as soon as possible</li>
	</ul>
	</li>
	<li>We need to differentiate administrations (and accompanying data) within MedicationRequest
	<ul>
		<li>Epic spec for API we are using: <a href="https://fhir.epic.com/Specifications?api=997" title="smart-link" class="external-link" rel="nofollow noreferrer">https://fhir.epic.com/Specifications?api=997</a></li>
		<li>Official HL7 page for the spec: <a href="https://hl7.org/fhir/us/core/STU4/StructureDefinition-us-core-medicationrequest.html" title="smart-link" class="external-link" rel="nofollow noreferrer">https://hl7.org/fhir/us/core/STU4/StructureDefinition-us-core-medicationrequest.html</a>
		<ul>
			<li>Epic may have extended beyond this, but serves as a baseline</li>
		</ul>
		</li>
		<li>It appears the “category” field may be able to filter it (“inpatient” or “outpatient”) - validate</li>
	</ul>
	</li>
	<li>Querying for antineoplastic/anticancer drugs in MedicationRequest
	<ul>
		<li><tt>clean_therapy_name</tt> and <tt>split_therapy_name</tt> can probably be used as-is to create search regex for specific drugs in MedicationRequest tables</li>
		<li>They were based on the <tt>systemic_therapy</tt> data, not the SPMD med admins per se, so the regexes they help create should work against a new source, but it is probably best to verify (see matching below)</li>
	</ul>
	</li>
	<li>Therapy name normalization: SPMD’s med admins were normalized to the <tt>systemic_therapy.therapy_name</tt> values using <tt>ca.map_drugproduct</tt> (see <a href="https://docs.google.com/spreadsheets/d/17G3rTmy56ZX11vZAA6gXBP4yvrhNxbEjLYyAI122lB8/edit?gid=1293297947#gid=1293297947" title="smart-link" class="external-link" rel="nofollow noreferrer">https://docs.google.com/spreadsheets/d/17G3rTmy56ZX11vZAA6gXBP4yvrhNxbEjLYyAI122lB8/edit?gid=1293297947#gid=1293297947</a>). This normalization probably needs to be expanded for the MedicationRequest data, but it hopefully covers some of the values</li>
	<li>Matching medication administrations. The algorithm for SPMD’s med admins is:
	<ul>
		<li>Med admin therapy matches one or more antineoplastics/anticancer meds for the cohort for one of the patients (query itself)</li>
		<li>Admin occurs on/after diagnosis date or is undated (check proportion of undated admins, should be low)</li>
		<li>Admin matches one or more of the patient’s specific systemic therapies (i.e., patient-specific therapy regex or exact match)</li>
		<li>The normalization and regexes needed for SPMD’s med admins may work again here (as above for the query), but may need to be adjusted</li>
	</ul>
	</li>
	<li>Potential new fields
	<ul>
		<li>Reason for discontinuation: poor population in SPMD’s med admins for Aurora/Ascension - if added validate Aurora/Ascension coverage</li>
		<li>Number of cycles / dose /  quantity
		<ul>
			<li>Some of this exists in SPMD’s med admins table, but it is not part of standard abstraction and so was not added to the <tt>medication_administration</tt> table. If this has changed or Merck needs this, we should add it.</li>
		</ul>
		</li>
	</ul>
	</li>
</ul>

            <br/>
        </td>
    </tr>
    </table>

    <br/>

